Sitting on approximately 2000 square meters piece of land located at the intersection of Thompson Avenue and McDonald Road, in the heart of highbrow Ikoyi in Lagos, the capital city of Nigeria, the Altona is a 6-floor residential development with 6 units of 3-bedroom flats, and 3 penthouses. Also Read: Emerald Continental Hotel Development in Victoria Island, Lagos, Nigeria Each unit has been crafted and finished to a high standard incorporating many desirable details from Italian and German-designed kitchens to Italian doors and tiles in all the bathrooms, bedrooms, and living areas. The penthouses also feature mood-control lighting and outdoor living areas.  The exceptional quality is also reflected in the services and facilities available e.g. the staff quarters, the secure electric gates and video entry phone system, the CCTV installed throughout, and the pre-wired alarm system of choice for all homes. Other facilities include a swimming pool, a fully fitted gym, and dedicated concierge and off-street secure parking for all residents, as well as ample visitor parking outside in addition to Valet parking for residents during daytime hours. Developer: Abigail Michael Project Managers: CCP LLP Architects: Idlewoods Procurement Consultant: IL Bagno Quantity Surveyors: Costec Consultants Mechanical / Electrical Consultants: Topklan Engineering Services Structural Engineers: Molcad Associates ELV, Fire and Access Control: Hausba Interior Designs: CC Interiors Main Contractor: Vita Construction M&E Contractor: SCS Solutions Building Foundation: Trevi Foundations Lifts and Elevators: Mitsui Lifts HVAC: Panaserve